⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Kalessin
node U1 · U1 · ⟦Kalessin:U1:0a5d9a⟧

WHO   — Kalessin — the Eldest
WHAT  — The great dragon who carries Ged and Lebannen home from Selidor, who returns the fire-scarred child Tehanu to her own people, and who keeps the memory of when dragon and human were one race, sundered by the Vedurnan.
WHERE — U1 · Le Guin  Framework inputs: Earthsea  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the deepest truth of Earthsea is that dragon and human are one divided kind — the dragons who kept the wild and the wind, the people who chose making and possession; because the breach must someday be healed.
HOW   — By flight on wings older than the kingdoms of men, by the Old Speech in which to speak is to make true, by bearing the worthy and burning the false — and by knowing Tehanu for its kin when no one else could.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  We were one people once, dragon and human — and I remember the wind before you chose the weight of gold.

